<input></input>  --> compulsory --> also can be written as shortcut <input /> if nothing inside 
component syntax --> {ChatInput()} == <ChatInput></ChatInput>
Fragment (<></>)= group elements together, without creating an extra <div>
props(properties) is an object containing all atributes given to the component 
in react when we give an array of component , each component should be given a key to track changes in the array
state - data connected to html, when data changes, html changes 
array of this state --> array[0] gives current value 
array[1] contains funcition that updates data --> updater funtion 
inr eact we copy the data and then modify rather than modifying the original data
...chatMessages --> copy of chatMessages array--> spread operator 
lifting state up - when we want to share data between components, we move the state to the closest common ancestor of the components that need it. This is called "lifting state up".
react uses className instead of class as "class" is a reserved keyword and react is basically javascript code. 
hooks insert react features into our component, react.usetate is a hook
hooks start with use
put hooks on top of the component 
hooks should not be inside anything fucntion or if 
useeffect lets us run some code after some code is created or updated 
dependency array used to let it know when to run a code when what changes, if it is empty then useeffect will run only when the elem created 
use ref lets us automatically save html element from the component 
ref is a container with special react features 
